 its equity portion the fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors it invests in growth and value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations for the fixedincome portion the fund invests in fixed income securities including bills notes bonds senior loans participation notes passthrough certificates assetbacked securities mortgagebacked securities and certificates of deposit issued by or guaranteed by companies governments their agencies and instrumentalities and multinational organizations it invests in debt securities with varying maturity and credit quality the fund employs fundamental analysis with a combination of topdown and bottomup security selection approach focusing on factors such as a countrys outlook for economic growth inflation interest rates currency regulatory framework political stability the supply and demand trends for various industries cash flow return on investments returns on invested capital health of balance sheets strong competitive advantages prospects for earnings growth strength of management sound financial management sound accounting policies pricing flexibility attractiveness of each investment opportunity general market political and economic conditions and expected future returns of investments to create its portfolio it benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the msci frontier markets index net tr and msci emerging markets index the fund employs proprietary research to create its portfolio it was formerly known as nile capital investment trust  nile pan africa fund nile capital investment trust  nile africa frontier and emerging fund was formed on april   and is domiciled in the united states detailed description  village boulevardsuite princeton nj united statesfounded in  phone  fax  nilefundscomourfunds key executives for nile capital investment trust  nile africa frontier and emerging fund mr larry seruma portfolio manager compensation as of fiscal year  similar private compan